snippet.textDisplay:
To you reading this, the moments around other people when you feel you need to pretend, when you wish you were funnier or more interesting; that fear right there will suck the joy right out of your life.
Niall has a point here:
be yourself, warts and all, because the alternative is to be alienated from yourself by trying to behave in ways you think will appeal to others so they won't judge you.

It really comes down to this choice: be yourself and experience the rejection that is inevitable (because no matter how lovely you are, some people will disapprove of you), or be unhappy whilst pretending.
